{
  "texts": [
    "This paper is structured to provide a comprehensive and systematic review of the application of artificial intelligence (AI) in the insurance industry, with a focus on automotive, health, and property insurance domains.",
    "Section 2 investigates the theoretical background, exploring the foundational frameworks that underpin the integration of AI in insurance, including technology acceptance and adoption, risk management and decision-making, sustainable and responsible AI, and cognitive and behavioral dimensions.",
    "Section 3 presents a detailed literature review of AI applications in insurance, categorized by academic research and industrywide adoption, highlighting key findings and methodologies across different insurance sectors.",
    "Section 4 outlines the methodology employed for this systematic review, following the PRISMA guidelines to ensure rigorous and unbiased analysis.",
    "Section 5 discusses the significant findings from the review, comparing academic research with industry implementations and identifying key gaps and opportunities."
  ]
}